author: liyin
msg: [0.89-fb] [ HBASE-7517] Do not throw PreemptiveFastFailExceptions when caused by another PFFE
Sometimes, if we are looking up a region in META, and both META  and
ROOT are unavailable, then the PFFE thrown by root's unavailability seems
to gets caught in the same function and is processed twice. We should avoid
this to prevent the race condition that liyin mentioned.
